com.samsung.android.sdk.healthdata

Interface HealthConstants.BloodGlucose

  • All Superinterfaces:
    HealthConstants.Common, HealthConstants.DiscreteMeasurement
    Enclosing class:
    HealthConstants

    public static interface HealthConstants.BloodGlucose
extends HealthConstants.DiscreteMeasurement
    This interface defines blood glucose data of user.

    Properties of the following extending interfaces are available for this data type.

    • HealthConstants.Common
    • HealthConstants.DiscreteMeasurement

    Properties

    Blood glucose data has the following properties.
    See more common properties by spreading this section out.

      Property name Description
      HealthConstants.BloodGlucose.UUID [Mandatory]
      Data's unique ID,
      assigned by the system when new data is inserted
      HealthConstants.BloodGlucose.CREATE_TIME [Mandatory]
      Data's created time in the health data store,
      assigned by the system when new data is inserted
      HealthConstants.BloodGlucose.UPDATE_TIME [Mandatory]
      Data's updated time in the health data store,
      assigned by the system when new data is updated
      HealthConstants.BloodGlucose.PACKAGE_NAME [Mandatory]
      Application package name which provides data,
      assigned by the system when new data is inserted
      HealthConstants.BloodGlucose.DEVICE_UUID [Mandatory]
      Device identifier of the source device which provides health data
      HealthConstants.BloodGlucose.START_TIME [Mandatory]
      UTC Time when the measurement is started
      HealthConstants.BloodGlucose.TIME_OFFSET [Mandatory]
      Time offset which considers time zone and daylight saving time
      HealthConstants.BloodGlucose.GLUCOSE [Mandatory]
      Measured blood glucose value
      HealthConstants.BloodGlucose.MEAL_TIME UTC Time at which meal is taken
      HealthConstants.BloodGlucose.MEAL_TYPE Context information for meal
      HealthConstants.BloodGlucose.MEASUREMENT_TYPE Type of the sample blood
      HealthConstants.BloodGlucose.SAMPLE_SOURCE_TYPE Source type of the blood vessel where the sample is taken
      HealthConstants.BloodGlucose.COMMENT Comment

    Data Permission

    Data permission acquisition for this data type is required toread or write data.
    See Permission Manager and request data permission.
    Since:
    1.0.0

          • MEAL_TYPE_AFTER_SNACK
          • MEAL_TYPE_BEFORE_SLEEP

        Is the blood glucose data's meal type shown differently on S Health?

        The meal type of inserted blood glucose data can be shown differently on S Health because its UI policy can be changed when S Health is updated. E.g. Blood glucose data that is saved with MEAL_TYPE_BEFORE_BREAKFAST can be shown as Pre-meal on S Health and MEAL_TYPE_AFTER_SNACK can be shown as General. But it doesn't affect to data. Its meal type is MEAL_TYPE_BEFORE_BREAKFAST as it is.

        Since:
